US LAW FIRM CLOSURES

In the wake of the collapse of New York firm Mudge Rose, two more US
firms have gone under. In New York, 20 lawyer-firm Townley & Updike
announced it is shutting its doors following the failure of merger
talks with Coudert Brothers and Winthrop Stimson Putnam & Roberts. In
Philadelphia, Cohen Shapiro Polisher Sheikamn & Cohen has closed after
suffering some important staff defections. Recently, a group of 21
lawyers moved over to rival firm Drinker Biddle & Reath. At the time of
the closure, the firm had 66 lawyers.

