January 1, 1994

OKLAHOMA SEEKING DIRECTOR OF SUBSTANCE
ABUSE PROGRAMS

The Oklahoma Department of Mental Health and Substance Abuse
Services is seeking a Director of Substance Abuse Programs. The
position has a salary range of $52,000 to $62,000. Requirements for
the job are completion of studies for a master's degree in psychology,
sociology, social work, or a closely related field plus eight years of
administrative experience in substance abuse programs, including at
least three years in planning and directing a substance abuse program
in a community setting. Resumes must be received by January 14.
Send them to the Personnel Manager, Oklahoma Department of Mental
Health and Substance Abuse Services, P.O. Box 53277, Oklahoma
City, OK 73152.



