ENERGY WEEK '96 FOCUSES ON TECHNOLOGICAL ADVANCEMENTS

Rapid changes within the energy industry - oil, gas,
alternative fuels, and petrochemicals -- are having a major
impact both technologically and geographically. The ENERGY
WEEK'96 Conference & Exhibition, the world's largest event to
focus on current and future technologies for these industries,
attests to the significant advances underway around the globe.
It will also explore CAD/CAM/CIM technologies as applied to
energy industries. It will be held January 29-February 2,
1996, at the George R.  Brown Convention Center in Houston,
Texas.

This year, for the first time, the event is being sponsored
jointly by three major organizations -- the American Society
of Mechanical Engineers (ASME International), the American
Petroleum Institute (API), and PennWell Conferences and
Exhibitions (a division of PennWell Publishing Company).

For more information, call (212)705-8157.



