Thiokol and The Carlyle Group have closed on

Thiokol and The Carlyle Group have closed on
their $750-million purchase of Howmet
Corporation from France's Pechiney. Thiokol
holds the minority stake in the venture but
according to the agreement with Carlyle can
buy out the merchant banker in three years.
Each organization has reportedly anted $100
million, "financing the $550 million balance
with non-recourse debt and the issuance of
preferred stock."




